Samsung in $ 400 mln China venture . South Korea ' s Samsung Display Devices Co , a unit of Samsung Group , said on Wednesday it would spend $ 400 million to build a colour picture tube plant in Tianjin , China . Samsung said in a statement it would set up Tianjin Samsung Display Devices Co , in which Tianjin City Electronics and Instruments Industrial General Co would hold a combined 20 percent stake and Samsung the remainder . Construction would begin in the second half of next year for the completion in 1998 , the statement said . The plant will produce 1 . 2 million colour picture tubes and 1 . 8 million colour display tubes annually . Samsung , the world ' s largest maker of colour television picture tubes , has plants in Malaysia , Germany and Mexico , and plans factories in Shenzhen , China , and in Manaus , Brazil . 
